article.description: Khara Smith scored 24 points and Jenni Dant added 20 to lead No. 24 DePaul past South Florida, 63-57.
article.headline: DePaul remains perfect in C-USA play
article.linkText: DePaul rallies in second half to edge South Florida
article.story:
CHICAGO (AP) -- Khara Smith scored a career-high 24 points and
had seven rebounds as DePaul (No. 24 ESPN/USA Today, No. 25 AP) defeated South Florida 63-57 on Sunday afternoon.

	   DePaul (14-4, 3-0 Conference USA) trailed for most of the first
half until closing out the period with a 15-2 run that gave it a
33-27 lead.

	   Smith scored 12 points in the first half. South Florida (5-11,
0-3) shot 56 percent from the field in the first half and was
4-of-6 from 3-point range.

	   Aiya Shepard cut the DePaul lead to 60-57 with 1:07 left in the
game. South Florida had a chance to come within one, but Sonia
Cotton missed with 17 seconds left. Shepard led South Florida with
16 points, and Cotton added 11.

	   DePaul has won seven of its past eight and has a 9-0 home
record. Jenni Dant also scored 20 points.
